Purpose
This file is the recursive execution loop of the framework.

Linear intent
1. Open `Lwt.Syntax` so the file can use sequential async style.
2. Define `log_decision` so every routing choice is written through the runtime logger.
3. In `loop`, receive the injected runtime services in addition to the configuration and registry.
4. Ask the decider for the current route from the current configuration, context, and payload.
5. Log the chosen decision before acting on it.
6. If the decision is `Stop`, return the current payload and context as the final result.
7. If the decision is `Next agent`, run one agent through the runtime engine and pass the shared services through.
8. Record that single outcome into the context.
9. Recurse with the updated context and the new payload produced by the agent.
10. If the decision is `Parallel agents`, run all selected agents through the parallel executor while sharing the same runtime services.
11. Record all outcomes into the context.
12. Record one extra event that marks the parallel join point.
13. Merge the items into one batch payload through the aggregator.
14. Recurse with the updated context and the merged payload.

